# Project Context

Fitness management platform. Backend is Laravel (REST API), frontend is React Native (Expo).
High throughput: 1000+ classes/day, 20+ attendees each, concurrent writes from multiple staff.

## Engineering Principles
- Prioritize clean, readable, maintainable code over cleverness.
- Enforce separation of responsibilities; keep controllers thin.
- Consider scalability and concurrency in every design decision.
- Avoid unnecessary database operations; favor efficient queries.
- Document any assumptions made where requirements are ambiguous.
- All non-trivial logic must be covered by automated tests.
- Handle errors and edge cases early with guard clauses; keep the happy path last.

## Architecture
- Backend: layered architecture. Controllers (HTTP only) → Form Requests (validation) → Services/Actions (business logic) → Eloquent Models (persistence) → API Resources (response shaping). Controllers must not contain business logic or query building.
- Frontend: feature-based structure. Separate presentation (components) from data access (hooks/services) and state. No API calls inline in components.
- Single responsibility per class/module; prefer composition over inheritance.
- Dependencies point inward: business logic never depends on framework-specific HTTP or UI details.

## Naming Conventions
### Backend (Laravel / PHP)
- Classes: PascalCase. Controllers end in `Controller`, services in `Service`, single-use actions in `Action`, form requests in `Request`, resources in `Resource`.
- Methods & variables: camelCase. Booleans read as predicates (`isAttended`, `hasCheckedIn`).
- Database tables: plural snake_case; columns snake_case; primary keys `id`; foreign keys `<singular>_id`.
- Routes: kebab-case, plural nouns, RESTful verbs over custom action names.

### Frontend (React Native / Expo)
- Components & their files: PascalCase. Hooks: camelCase prefixed with `use`.
- Variables & functions: camelCase; event handlers prefixed `handle` (`handleToggle`).
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE. Types/interfaces: PascalCase.

## Consistency
- One naming style per layer—do not mix conventions within a file.
- Names describe intent, not implementation; avoid abbreviations and filler words.